Anyway, we rolled back the fourth-sub rule after that. Here's a longer look at how it all went down.

Then, this happens: 1. GK Tim Howard swaps jerseys with midfielder Mark Lisi 2. Winger Eddie Gaven subs in (with GK kit + gloves), replacing Lisi in goal 3. Howard and Gaven swap jerseys, with Howard back in goal 4. Gaven scores the winner nine minutes into extra time

So, we used to allow four subs in a game‚Äîthree field players, one GK‚Äîlong before a fourth sub in extra time became a thing. RFK Stadium, July 2003. The MetroStars are tied with DC at the end of regulation, and the visitors have made all three of their field-player subs‚Ä¶
